shady
Homonym Number:
Word Class:adjective
Sense Number:
Definition:used of a hillside, face, land etc which does not get full sun; usually of a Southern aspect. Often almost in combination in, e.g. <i>shady country, shady face </i>
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
